# tshy — Isaac Z. Schlueter's "TypeScript HYbridizer - Hybrid
#        (CommonJS/ESM) TypeScript node package builder" — a
#        TypeScript-Node build tool that produces DUAL-FORMAT
#        npm packages with simultaneous CommonJS (.cjs / .d.cts)
#        AND ECMAScript Module (.mjs / .d.mts) outputs from a
#        single TypeScript source tree, with proper
#        package.json `exports` field wiring for Node 16+'s
#        conditional-exports resolution.
#        Distinguishing from tsc, tsup, unbuild, esbuild,
#        microbundle, and other TypeScript bundlers by:
#          - HYBRID DUAL-FORMAT OUTPUT — produces BOTH:
#              * dist/commonjs/  → .cjs + .d.cts files
#              * dist/esm/       → .mjs + .d.mts files
#            with package.json `exports` field auto-populated
#            with conditional-exports map:
#              "exports": {
#                ".": {
#                  "import": {
#                    "types": "./dist/esm/index.d.mts",
#                    "default": "./dist/esm/index.mjs"
#                  },
#                  "require": {
#                    "types": "./dist/commonjs/index.d.cts",
#                    "default": "./dist/commonjs/index.cjs"
#                  }
#                }
#              }
#          - PROPER NODE 16+ MODULE RESOLUTION — generated
#            packages work in both `require()` and `import`
#            contexts WITHOUT runtime dual-package hazard
#            because tshy emits SEPARATE source-to-target
#            compilations for each format (not a wrapper or
#            interop layer)
#          - AUTOMATIC PACKAGE.JSON `exports` SYNCHRONIZATION
#            — tshy reads source-tree structure + tshy config
#            from package.json and writes the appropriate
#            `exports` map; no manual maintenance of
#            conditional-exports
#          - WATCH MODE via --watch / -w — uses chokidar to
#            watch ./src for changes and rebuilds incrementally
#            on file create / write / remove / rename
#          - TYPESCRIPT NATIVE PREVIEW INTEGRATION — depends
#            on @typescript/native-preview (tsgo) for fast
#            native-Rust TypeScript compilation in addition to
#            stock typescript
#          - DIALECT-AWARE — set-folder-dialect.ts marks
#            subdirectories as "commonjs" or "module" via
#            per-folder package.json files; tshy honors these
#            for correct module resolution
#          - MINIMAL OPCODE BINARY (bin-min.mjs) — distributed
#            binary is bundled to a single .mjs file for fast
#            startup; no transpilation cost at invocation
#          - NO BUNDLER — unlike tsup / esbuild / rollup, tshy
#            does NOT bundle dependencies; it preserves the
#            module graph so npm `node_modules` resolution
#            works normally
#          - BlueOak-1.0.0 LICENSE — Isaac's preferred
