#           library" — Paul Miller (paulmillr on GitHub).
#           Distinct from notify (R653, Rust Axis 17 opener)
#           and fsnotify (R654, Go Axis 17 expansion) by being:
#              1. WRAPS NODE.JS fs.watch + fs.watchFile — Node
#                 has built-in fs.watch (event-based, via
#                 inotify/FSEvents/etc.) and fs.watchFile
#                 (polling-based).  Both have quirks across
#                 platforms.  chokidar abstracts these into a
#                 single reliable API that "just works" on
#                 Linux/macOS/Windows.
#              2. EVENT-EMITTER API — Watcher EXTENDS
#                 EventEmitter and emits:
#                   'add'         — file added
#                   'change'      — file modified
#                   'unlink'      — file removed
#                   'addDir'      — directory added
#                   'unlinkDir'   — directory removed
#                   'ready'       — initial scan complete
#                   'raw'         — raw underlying event
#                   'error'       — error during watching
#                 Distinct from notify's closure callback and
#                 fsnotify's Go channels.
#              3. GLOB PATTERN MATCHING built-in — chokidar
#                 watch() accepts paths, glob patterns, or
#                 arrays:
#                   import { watch } from 'chokidar'
#                   const watcher = watch([
#                     'src/**/*.ts',
#                     '!src/**/*.test.ts',
#                     'package.json'
#                   ], { ignoreInitial: true })
#                 Internally uses anymatch + minimatch for
#                 pattern resolution.  Distinct from notify
#                 (no pattern support) and fsnotify (no pattern
#                 support).
#              4. POLLING FALLBACK via `usePolling: true` —
#                 some environments (NFS, virtual filesystems,
#                 Docker for Mac on macOS) have unreliable
#                 fs.watch events; chokidar's usePolling
#                 option falls back to interval-based polling.
#                 Distinct from notify (PollWatcher variant
#                 separate API) and fsnotify (no polling).
#              5. AWAIT-WRITE-FINISH for atomic file writes —
#                 some editors write to a temp file then
#                 rename; chokidar's awaitWriteFinish option
#                 waits for the file to stop changing before
#                 emitting 'change', preventing partial-write
#                 events during editor saves.
#              6. ignored OPTION with FUNCTION OR GLOB —
#                 ignored: (path) => /node_modules/.test(path)
#                 or ignored: '**/node_modules/**'
#                 Distinct from notify + fsnotify which require
#                 manual filtering after event reception.
#              7. CHOKIDAR v4 MINIMAL CORE — chokidar v4 (2024)
#                 dramatically shrunk dependencies; v3 had ~6
#                 deps, v4 has only `readdirp`.  Reflects Paul
#                 Miller's noble-cryptography minimalism ethos.
